The ABC13 Vaccine Tracker shows that about 13.9 million people across Texas are fully vaccinated against COVID-19 as of Sep.5. About 16.7 million people statewide have received at least one dose.

Statewide, ABC13s analysis shows the number of people fully vaccinated is about 48.1% of all Texas residents.

The data shows the share of Texas residents 12 or over who are now fully vaccinated is about 57.8%. In May, the federal government approved the first vaccines for people ages 12-15, but it remains unavailable to children under 12.

You can now search every vaccine provider with shots available today in Texas in our searchable map below. Its updated every morning to show only those locations with vaccines in stock.

How is Texas doing getting everyone vaccinated?

The pace of vaccinations has slowed. Over the last seven days, the data show an average of 36,818 people per day became fully vaccinated, compared to 44,493 people per day the seven days before that. Thats a change of -17.2%.

You can see the percentage of all people vaccinated day-by-day in the chart below.

The CDC data is updated daily, but the agency says its total number of vaccinations could be behind actual doses administered by up to 72 hours based on when it receives data from state and local health departments.

Whats happening in my Texas county?

You can look up the progress thus far in every Texas county below. Start typing your county name in the search bar to find it faster. These county totals, from the CDC, include doses from state and federal government providers and only include the countys residents.

If I am eligible, where can I get vaccinated?

At least 3,650 pharmacies, medical facilities and other providers have vaccines in stock across Texas. You can search all of them in our live map, which pulls data every morning from the VaccineFinder system at the CDCs vaccines.gov.

The yellow and green circles show clusters of locations. If you click them, the map will zoom in to show individual locations. Clicking a red marker will show the vaccine locations name, address and ways to get more information online or by phone.

You can use the search button at top right to zoom to your address or zip code.

Source: VaccineFinder, Boston Childrens Hospital. Data 2021. Boston Childrens Hospital. All rights reserved.

If you want to learn more about how state officials are administering vaccines, you can click here (or scroll to the bottom to see a link) to learn more about the states vaccination strategy.
